The more we learned, the more amazed we were.

The female body is _extraordinary_. The way your body knows how to grow a baby, how to time labor, how colostrum changes composition in the first days to match exactly what your newborn needs, how skin-to-skin contact regulates a baby's temperature and heart rate, how the microbiome transfer during vaginal birth seeds your baby's immune system.

God really knew what He was doing. Every child is a miracle, and the physiology behind it all is incredible. Science is still discovering more, but what we already know is stunning.

Moms, you were built for this.

#line(length: 100%)

This book is the consolidated guide we wished existed when I was pregnant. It's not medical advice — we're not doctors, and we're not pretending to be. It's a consolidation of the research, organized as an actionable resource for normal people. Every claim is cited. Every major viewpoint is represented. Read what applies to you, skip what doesn't.

We'll give you the science, what your providers will tell you, _and_ what they might not know or might not share. Most of the decisions in this book are genuinely value judgments — there's no single right answer, and we present the options so you can decide what's right for your family. But for some topics, the evidence on what's best for a baby's health and development is pretty clear. When that's the case, we'll tell you. We're not going to hide behind false balance when the research points in one direction. That doesn't mean the "optimal" choice is always the right choice for your situation — there are always tradeoffs, and we cover those too. But you deserve to know what the evidence says, and we're not going to sugarcoat it.

#line(length: 100%)

The first days of your child's life are among the most important for their development. The decisions you make during pregnancy and birth matter. Not because there's one right answer, but because _your_ answer should be informed, intentional, and yours.

Whatever you decide on any given topic in this book, make those decisions thoughtfully. Talk about them with your partner. Bring your questions to your provider. Read the research. Then trust yourself.

This book is for you and your partner to read, discuss, and decide together. That's how we used the research that became this book — side by side, figuring it out as a team.

I'm glad my husband built this. I hope it helps your family the way it helped ours.

